@BatMeckley, @cian riordan, @Rollmottle, @Nomograph Mastering, @Ross Fortune, @sethearnest…. This list goes on and if I try to include everyone I know I’m gonna leave out someone. 

I learn shit from you guys every day, about how to make better music and be a better human, how to think and listen and give a shit about things that matter. 

The info here is expensive, but the people are fucken priceless.

@Nomograph Mastering . Yaaar. Very nicely put man . I agree v much with what you’ve said . 

And within what you’ve said , I feel it caters to my concern . Which is , when I see people encouraging other creatives  to pour everything they’ve got (and more ) into external validation , within a business as hard nosed as the music business , I worry  a little that it might just break them and their love for the art 

My mrs is on the business side of the music game and it’s all paid maternity , health care and salaries . So it’s quite the juxtaposition seeing what young artists are being encouraged to sacrifice atm …

@Nomograph Mastering  As a result of this convo I hunted down Paul’s GS posts on this. Now, I’m going to have to learn about what floating point really means and what is a “mantissa”. The subject of his  knowledge is fascinating . 
quote :” If your mix is sounding bad the more stuff you put into it, it may be because the stuff itself is flawed, inappropriate and/or low quality processing. But it sure as hell isn't because of the precision of the system itself.” P. Frindle 

Dope

