I’ve noticed myself auditioning plugins or doing experiments when I am avoiding digging into whatever task is in front of me. Makes me wonder how often I’ve done this unconsciously.

I’ve also experienced seasons where I’ve consciously engaged in exploration from a healthy (non-avoiding) place and it’s resulted in some pretty big growth. Especially when other people are involved.

@Nomograph Mastering I’ve heard you say lots of things to the effect that “you’ve gone down a lot of rabbit holes.” Do you count any of that as wasted time or do you just think of it as part of the journey?
